valid="yes">III, 4, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 92</bibl>.<lb />Used in the sense of heaven: <cit><quote>the fated s. gives us free scope,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.232" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 232</bibl></cit> (rhyming). Considered as the region to which the souls of the departed rise: <cit><quote>my soul and body to the --es and ground,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1199" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1199</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my soul is in the s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.308" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 308</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.7.21" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 7, 21</bibl>. cf. <emph>they</emph> (curses) <cit><quote>ascend the s. and there awake God's gentle-sleeping peace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.287" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 287</bibl></cit>.
